                <head>No. 14.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">White</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-04-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 9, 1888</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Bayard stated, in reply to Mr. White’s telegram of April 7, that this
                    Government did not object to the extension of the arrangement for the protection
                    of the fur-seal fisheries to the whole of Behring Sea.</p>
            </div>
